column51: Some things aren't intuitive. I wanted to see what $5 books there were for the coupon but I was immediately sure how to do that. But the things I wanted by name I just looked them up and added them to the cart just fine.    And recently someone pointed out to me how this might discourage reading for kids who can't afford the book fairs and see friends buying books that can't. Some children may feel unworthy of reading. I love the book. fairs but if your are ever thinking about handling that. Having families fill a gift card. And kids that can't afford could be give a card with enough to buy one or two books. I would be willing to donate toward that as a parent who is able to buy children books.

column51: I got on to review a student order from December that I owe shipping for. I was not able to locate it. I called customer service who was able to see the order. Not sure why I cannot see the order. I was told I need to pay shipping on this student order because it was under $25. I received an email yesterday from an agent that said shipping is included on orders under $25, These are both contradicting themselves. It's very frustrating that I, as a teacher, have to pay for an order that is one of my students when the book cost $9 (under $25 where shipping is included)...a quote from the agent's email yesterday. Shipping included means the cost of shipping is calculated in the price of the book/order. I will be calling back after school to speak to a supervisor.
